body:

# **💙 A huge Thank You to Our Reviewers**

Behind every PyCon DE & PyData program is a vast amount of invisible effort that makes it all possible.

Before a single talk appears on the schedule, hundreds of proposals are carefully read, evaluated, and discussed. This process is what helps us build a program that is not only diverse, but also relevant, practical, and valuable for the community.

And this work would not be possible without our reviewers.

## **What reviewers actually do**

Each proposal goes through multiple reviews.  
Reviewers assess:

* clarity and structure of the talk  
* technical depth and relevance  
* originality and practical value  
* fit for our audience (primarily mid-to-senior developers)

They don’t just score submissions — they provide context, voice concerns, highlight strong ideas, and help the Program Committee make informed decisions.

It’s a thoughtful and time-consuming process, done alongside their full-time jobs.

